:INFO
The Great Migration Told Through Three Lives
Isabel Wilkerson spent fifteen years on this book and it shows in every page. \
The Warmth of Other Suns follows three people who left the Jim Crow South in \
different decades: Ida Mae Brandon in 1937, George Swanson Starling in 1945, \
and Robert Joseph Pershing Foster in 1953. Each journey is different and the \
same. The structural choice of following individuals through a sixty-year migration \
makes the largest internal migration in American history feel the size of a life.

